IEYMgmGjnkmaC877lgnx4M37KQyq-WeecYwYRLM=\\\",\\\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering workflow refinements**\\\\n\\\\nThe user mentioned that there might not be coverage because the external workflow didn't include a commit. I definitely want to make meaningful refinements. Adding a `@BeforeAll` seems like an idea, but I wonder if that’s the right move. There might be a potential issue with the AssertJ line involving `assertThat(SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(parent, SimpleTagSupport.class)).isSameAs(grandparent);` on the first invocation. Perhaps exploring a custom subclass and interface target could help solve the problem.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing imports and types**\\\\n\\\\nI see that the current branch is returning null, which is interesting. So this branch might not need to import JspTag? The class still appears to utilize JspTag, though. Perhaps avoiding the JspTag.class constant in the test is a good idea. However, since methods still use SimpleTagSupport, maybe I can sidestep using the JspTag variable type altogether. Would using Object be a better alternative? I'm pondering that!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_8RqEQLqz8NJ6UPYaCWnMk7hd|fc_0f0e05c6db090b1a0169f14230089481929bf5bb5df49430a3\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/SimpleTagSupportTest.java\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1228, \"output\": 1673, \"cacheRead\": 15872, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 18773, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777418773977, \"responseId\": \"resp_0f0e05c6db090b1a0169f142166fac8192ae99c03538e810cf\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-25-16-214779Z.log:1713:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_8RqEQLqz8NJ6UPYaCWnMk7hd|fc_0f0e05c6db090b1a0169f14230089481929bf5bb5df49430a3\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage jspapi.jsp_api;\\n\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.JspTag;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class SimpleTagSupportTest {\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void findsAncestorUsingPublicSimpleTagParentChain() {\\n        SimpleTagSupport grandparent = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        SimpleTagSupport parent = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        SimpleTagSupport child = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        parent.setParent(grandparent);\\n        child.setParent(parent);\\n\\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, SimpleTagSupport.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\\n        assertThat(SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(parent, SimpleTagSupport.class)).isSameAs(grandparent);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void returnsNullWhenNoMatchingAncestorExists() {\\n        SimpleTagSupport tag = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n\\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(tag, SimpleTagSupport.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isNull();\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777418802069}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-25-16-214779Z.log:1714:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_8RqEQLqz8NJ6UPYaCWnMk7hd|fc_0f0e05c6db090b1a0169f14230089481929bf5bb5df49430a3\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage jspapi.jsp_api;\\n\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.JspTag;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class SimpleTagSupportTest {\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void findsAncestorUsingPublicSimpleTagParentChain() {\\n        SimpleTagSupport grandparent = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        SimpleTagSupport parent = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        SimpleTagSupport child = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        parent.setParent(grandparent);\\n        child.setParent(parent);\\n\\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, SimpleTagSupport.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\\n        assertThat(SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(parent, SimpleTagSupport.class)).isSameAs(grandparent);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void returnsNullWhenNoMatchingAncestorExists() {\\n        SimpleTagSupport tag = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n\\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(tag, SimpleTagSupport.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isNull();\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777418802069}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-25-16-214779Z.log:1715:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering workflow refinements**\\n\\nThe user mentioned that there might not be coverage because the external workflow didn't include a commit. I definitely want to make meaningful refinements. Adding a `@Befor